FBIS4-63843 "drsov101_a_94044" FBIS-SOV-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 RUSSIAN INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Foreign Ministry Declares Support for Yemen's Unity Foreign Ministry Declares Support for Yemen's Unity LD2405144694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1346 GMT 24 May 94 LD2405144694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Vyacheslav Akimov] [Text] Moscow, 24 May (ITAR-TASS) -- "Russia supports the unity and stability of Yemen". The ITAR-TASS correspondent was told today by a representative of the Russian Federation Ministry of Foreign Affairs that this was contained in a message from the Russian leadership which was conveyed to 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council of the Republic of Yemen, yesterday by the Russian ambassador to Yemen. It notes in the message that Russia follows the development of events in Yemen attentively and is concerned over the continuing military operations and senseless fratricidal bloodshed, as a result of which hundreds of people have perished. Moscow, the message says, calls for a cease-fire and supports the unity of the entire people of Yemen.
